 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uteauvian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teauvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whiny<s>, spoiled</s> brat.</span><br>  Posts: 664<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 3:41:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> re-roll as a ranger...everybody <p>~~Teauvian~~<BR>
'You gonna bark all day little doggy or are you gonna bite?' -Mr. Blonde</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uhighlanderdragonbear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Highlander Dragonbear</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Master</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 3:53:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/ysanne/pics/headshots/headhighlanderrnew.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The next patch</span><hr size=1> To the Everquest Developement Team,<br>
<br>
<br>
   I would like to address the Rods of Mystical Transvergence issue.  These Mod Rods have opened the doors for many smaller guilds to be able to do encounters that otherwise larger guilds would be able to do.  This seriously cuts down the content many smaller guilds are now able to do.  Mods Rods are a viable tactic for some.  Let me illustrate with a few examples.<br>
<br>
1.)  Guilds that have less than 5 full time clerics available per raid situation can do many things guilds with 5+ clerics can do to a certain extent.  While you might say some major encounters should require 5-10 clerics to do, guilds with less than 5 shouldn't even try to achieve what they can based on the 1 strategic magician that they can employ.  This still does not mean that a cleric or 2 will die and thus cause the raid to wipe, this can still happen.<br>
<br>
2.)  Mod rods greatly reduce the amount of time a raid can get back up to operational status after a wipeout.  Afterall, this reduces the endurance factor, does it not?<br>
<br>
3.)  You now make it sound that lots of magicians were crying because of this mod rod spell.  I do not believe this is the case.  While your statement might have truth in the fact that magicians are not able to employ their DD's and pets in combat because of their &quot;mod rod&quot; role, this does not mean that every magician in a guild has to be making the mod rods, only takes 1 and the rest can alternate each raid on making the rods.  Fix pet pathing, there are still situations that pets take the most stupid and annoying pathing during encounters and Beastlord pets seem to disappear at times as well as magician pets, off roaming somewhere and cannot be issued commands.<br>
<br>
4.)  Do not make the new mod rod a one minute buff.  This now takes up 1 buff slot and during raid encounters, the 15 buffs limitation are usually full or near full and heal over time spells usually are saved for the last spot thus cutting down the available buffs on a raid to 14.  This will now cut that down to 13.<br>
<br>
5.)  On the issue of No Drop rods that are target based summoned.  Handing Clerics an item, whether it be a mod rod or not, is a bad thing.  This messes up their targetting and could be bad on laggy situations and might cause a missed complete heal on the intended target and the magician is now the recipient on a complete heal.  Also, to cut down on lag during raids, some people have to turn off PC names.  Thus making this spell target summoned means people will have to keep names turned on so they can differentiate which &lt;random race&gt; Cleric of the many that look alike they need to target to summon a mod rod onto.<br>
<br>
6.)  Magicians as damage dealers and masters of the elements.  Magicians are not 2nd in damage dealers to Wizards, they are actually 3rd, Druids have an advantage over magicians.  A druid has a higher DD spell than magicians and a slew of DoT's to use whereas a Magician has 1 DoT and a smaller DD.  The pet might make up the difference, but I do not beleive that is the case.  Also, on the issue of masters of the elements, Magicians have no Ice based spells.  There are encounters in Everquest that Magicians are unable to land spells on.  Example, Gozzrem in West wing of Temple of Veeshan.  Ice hits good on that encounter while fire is usually resisted or hits for very little, thus making Magicians pretty useless except for the pet.<br>
<br>
7.)  The issue with the pets:  fix pet pathing, there are still situations that pets take the most stupid and annoying pathing during encounters and Beastlord pets seem to disappear at times as well as magician pets, off roaming somewhere and cannot be issued commands.  Also, on large raid encounters, if there are lots of pets, Cleric Wizard Necromancer Magician Enchanter, the lag is greater and the area a melee has to be able to hit a mob is greatly reduced because of the pets.  It also cuts down mobility for players to be able to move around without being blocked out by the pets.  Thus, pets are usually left out of large raid encounters.  Make pets transparent so players could move freely past them and that solves that problem.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is in part what I e-mailed to SOE this evening. <p><img src=http://members.cox.net/ysanne/sigs/highlanderrsignew.gif
 border=0>

